  "name": "Ley Line Affinity",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Your magic naturally bonds to the overflowing power of ley lines, granting you strength even in regions your magic would not flourish.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Area Bound drawback.</p>\n<p><strong>Benefit:</strong> You may bond to a ley line with your Area Bound casting tradition drawback even if the ley line&#8217;s location is not the same type of location you would normally bond to (bonding to a ley line does not automatically attune you to the ley line).</p>\n<p>In addition, you gain a bonus on Spellcraft checks made to attune to a ley line equal to 1/2 your magic skill bonus (minimum 1). You may treat any ley line you have successfully attuned to as a bonded area for the Area Bound general casting drawback, allowing your magic to work normally within a number of miles of the ley line even if you are bound to another location. Normal: The Area Bound general casting drawback restricts the caster to a specific type of location when forming a bond with a new area.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> This drawback is not useful or appropriate in games without ley lines. A character interested in this drawback feat should speak with their GM before selecting this feat.</p>\n",
